title: Owners warn others about man allegedly selling infected dogs
text:
Owners are warning others about a man in Tacoma who is allegedly selling sick dogs.
A couple told KIRO 7 the golden-lab mix puppy they purchased was diagnosed with Parvo, which is a contagious disease.
Just interview heartbroken owners of this little guy, he has Parvo, others sold sick dogs too.. Story after football pic.twitter.com/loTvLqqFQe
â€” Henry Rosoff (@HenryKIRO7) October 9, 2015 The owners' 10-week-old dog has spent most of its time at a veterinary clinic and the owners already have spent nearly $3,000 to try and save the dog.
The couple has posted a warning on Craigslist about the seller. They received dozens of emails about the same thing happening to them.
Prayers for this little guy, about to speak with his owner... He's sick with Parvo, very devastating dog disease....
Posted by Henry Rosoff on Thursday, October 8, 2015
